http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/For-women-by-women/article13978749.ece

As many as 41 women artists, including prominent names such as P.S. Jalaja, Sara Hussain, Asha Nandan, besides artists and students from RLV College of Music and Fine Arts in Tripunithura, Sree Sankara University of Sanskrit, Kalady, and Fine Arts College, Thrissur — from across the State took part in a one-day art workshop organised by the district committee of the All Indian Democratic Women’s Association and Vanitha Sahithi at Rajendra Maidan on Saturday.The camp was held in the run-up to the ‘Women’s Parliament’ being organised at the Cochin International Airport auditorium on January 6.